47:// ccBalancerWrapper sits between the ClientConn and the Balancer.
48://
49:// ccBalancerWrapper implements methods corresponding to the ones on the
50:// balancer.Balancer interface. The ClientConn is free to call these methods
51:// concurrently and the ccBalancerWrapper ensures that calls from the ClientConn
52:// to the Balancer happen in order by performing them in the serializer, without
53:// any mutexes held.
54://
55:// ccBalancerWrapper also implements the balancer.ClientConn interface and is
56:// passed to the Balancer implementations. It invokes unexported methods on the
57:// ClientConn to handle these calls from the Balancer.
58://
59:// It uses the gracefulswitch.Balancer internally to ensure that balancer
60:// switches happen in a graceful manner.
